 Custom Overlay Creation for PYNQ-Z1 in Vivado
Start
  │
  ▼
Install Vivado & PYNQ-Z1 Board Files
  │
  ▼
Launch Vivado → Create New Project
  │
  ▼
Select PYNQ-Z1 Board
  │
  ▼
Create Block Design (IP Integrator)
  │
  ▼
Add ZYNQ7 Processing System
  │
  ▼
Run Block Automation → Apply Default PS Settings
  │
  ▼
Add IP Blocks (AXI GPIO ×3, AXI BRAM Controller)
  │
  ▼
Rename Blocks (e.g., leds, buttons, switches, bram)
  │
  ▼
Run Connection Automation
  │
  ▼
Verify Connections (GPIO ↔ LEDs, Buttons, Switches)
  │
  ▼
Create HDL Wrapper from Block Design
  │
  ▼
Run Synthesis → Implementation → Bitstream Generation
  │
  ▼
Export:
  • Block Design (.tcl)
  • Bitstream (.bit)
  • Hardware Description (.hwh)
  │
  ▼
Transfer Files to PYNQ-Z1 via SSH or File Transfer
  │
  ▼
Use Python (PYNQ API) to Control Custom Overlay
  │
  ▼
End
